
1/4 t  garlic salt
1   T  worcestershire
1.5 C  beef broth
1   T  ketchup

1  lb  beef
1   t  salt
1/4 t  pepper
1/2    yellow onion, diced

1/3 C  flour
7   T  apple juice
4   oz sliced mushrooms

1/2 C  sour cream

Combine 1/4 t garlic salt, 1T worcestershire sauce, 1 to 1.5 Cups
beef broth, and 1T ketchup, 1t salt, 1/4 t pepper.

Add to a crock pot with 1 lb beef and 1/2 diced onion.

Cook on low for 4-6 hours

Combine 1/3 C flour and 7T apple juice, add to the crock pot and MIX WELL.
Add 4 oz sliced mushrooms and stir.

Cook another 30 minutes.

Stir in 1/2 C sour cream and serve over noodles or rice.
